transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Viagra Score Blue. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: You know what? My name is Phil Kennedy. I called and ordered the—

Speaker 1: You called it bag or something. What was the letters after that?

Speaker 2: So if you're the newest formula from Pfizer, it's the Viagra AGV.

Speaker 1: Okay. Now, let me ask you something.

Speaker 2: My wife seen it on the email and says I already ordered that. I have this and it's called sildenafil.

Speaker 1: 100 milligram generic for Viagra. Is that the same stuff?

Speaker 2: So sildenafil is the leading ingredient in the original Viagra.

Speaker 1: It's the right ingredient in generics and it's also the lead ingredient in the AGV now.

Speaker 2: It's the inactive ingredients in each of these that make it a little bit different.

Speaker 1: Did you order the AGV? Yes, I do is what you're thinking. Okay. Well, sir—

Speaker 2: Let me pull up your prescription here and what's the, yeah, digging and see exactly what you ordered.

Speaker 1: And yeah, 'cause I got three bottles of this already. I don't want to—I don't want to duplicate what I ordered.

Speaker 2: Okay, so could you get your full name and date of birth?

Speaker 1: Phil Kennedy, C-A-I-N, I-D-Y.

Speaker 2: For 1256.

Speaker 1: Yeah, thank you, Phil.

Speaker 2: So I do see here the prescription was written by the doctor for a quantity of 25 of the 100 milligram Viagra AGV.

Speaker 1: Okay, so what's going—there's going to be a few differences with this pill.

Speaker 2: Did you by chance get the generic through sildenafil through Score Blue or through your home—

Speaker 1: Position?

Speaker 2: Rex MD was okay.

Speaker 1: So I've never worked with the Rex MD in particular.

Speaker 2: But the biggest thing to look at with these pills is to know where they're coming from, right?

Speaker 1: So AGV stands for authorized Viagra from France. Okay, so that's made under Pfizer.

Speaker 2: Okay, so the new pills themselves that you're receiving will say Greenstone on the bottom, right?

Speaker 1: That's the laboratory that's coming from, that's based in France and that's under Pfizer. That's how you—

Speaker 2: That's how you double-check the authenticity and the quality.

Speaker 1: Second, these pills will have the milligram dosage on them. So yours will say 100 most of the time.

Speaker 2: Generic sildenafil coming from the United States or Mexico has a code on the pill.

Speaker 1: Do you have your current prescription from the other company?

Speaker 2: Yeah, hold on. I'm opening the bottle right now. Okay, then I'll look.

Speaker 1: The oval pill has a code.

Speaker 2: Okay, three four three, hold on, and then the round pill—

Speaker 1: Is the same thing. It has a code.

Speaker 2: Correct. So that's how you know it's from a generic company that isn't authorized by the original patent.

Speaker 1: When it has a milligram dosage, that's how you know it's coming from the original producer.

Speaker 2: So these new pills will look different and be coming from a different place.

Speaker 1: However, it's kind of like, you know—

Speaker 2: It's—I'm just saying it's produced differently while it says sildenafil on it because that is the leading ingredient.

Speaker 1: There are other things in there that make it different. For the case of the AGV, the—

Speaker 2: Inactive ingredients make it break down faster, stays in your system longer, and also there's little to no side effects compared to the others.

Speaker 1: Hmm, well, I'm wondering if it's going to be any better than this.

Speaker 2: It's—

Speaker 1: Most patients that we have here at Score Blue, because we prescribe generic Viagra, we prescribe the TV, and we prescribe—

Speaker 2: Name brand, the blue pill, right? All of these options have different costs.

Speaker 1: So really, you know, you're paying for what you get for, right? Compared to generic and then the AGV.

Speaker 2: So most of our patients that have been prescribed generics in the past are moving over to the AGV because they're that happy with it.

Speaker 1: All right, then I'll leave it go.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay. Thank you.

Speaker 2: You're welcome, sir. Thank you.
